na, New Delhi, and Calicut. This move is designed to foster closer ties with customers and address the growing need for high-quality aluminium systems essential for today's architectural endeavors.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/brand-connect-initiative/alumil-india-outlines-2026-expansion-plans/129397819?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-149512/129397819.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "brand-connect-initiative"}]}